Package com.bakdata.dedupe.fusion

Class CommonConflictResolutions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bakdata.dedupe.fusion.CommonConflictResolutions
  • public final class CommonConflictResolutions
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides factory methods for common conflict resolutions. Usually, these methods are included through static imports.

    For new resolutions, please open an issue or PR on Github }.

      • max

        public static <T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>> ConflictResolution<T,​T> max()
        Selects all values that a maximal.

        This resolution may select multiple values that are equally maximal. These value retain their source tags. Use a successive first() to pick any value with the respective source information or use distinct().

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value.
        Returns:
        the maximal values.

      • first

        public static <T> TerminalConflictResolution<T,​T> first()
        Picks a the first value out of the bag of values. This resolution is mostly used as a tie-breaker to receive a TerminalConflictResolution.

        Note, ConflictResolution usually prevail order unless noted otherwise. If order is not prevailed, this method should be conceptional treated as random().

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value.
        Returns:
        the first value.

      • distinct

        public static <T> ConflictResolution<T,​T> distinct()
        Returns the list of values that are unique. Order is prevailed on the first occurrence.

        If a value appears multiple times, the resulting AnnotatedValue will have a calculated source.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value.
        Returns:
        the distinct values.
        See Also:
        AnnotatedValue.calculated(Object)

      • median

        public static <T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>> ConflictResolution<T,​T> median()
        Calculates the median value of a bag of conflicting numbers. If there are two median values, returns them both.

        Thus, in many cases using a successive mean() will yield the expected terminal resolution.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value.
        Returns:
        the median values.

      • merge

        public static <T> Merge.MergeBuilder<T> merge​(@NonNull
                                              @NonNull java.util.function.Supplier<T> instanceSupplier)
        Starts the creation of a Merge conflict resolution for record types. 
        Example: 
 ConflictResolution<Person, Person> personMerge = merge(Person::new)
   .field(Person::getId, Person::setId).with(min())
   .field(Person::getFirstName, Person::setFirstName).with(longest()).then(vote())
   .field(Person::getLastName, Person::setLastName).correspondingToPrevious()
   .build();
        Parameters:
        instanceSupplier - creates a new instance of the class.
        Returns:
        a new Merge.MergeBuilder.

      • merge

        public static <T> Merge.MergeBuilder<T> merge​(java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
        Starts the creation of a Merge conflict resolution for record types. 
        Example: 
 ConflictResolution<Person, Person> personMerge = merge(Person.class)
   .field(Person::getId, Person::setId).with(min())
   .field(Person::getFirstName, Person::setFirstName).with(longest()).then(vote())
   .field(Person::getLastName, Person::setLastName).correspondingToPrevious()
   .build();
        Parameters:
        clazz - the type of the record. Needs to have a public, parameterless constructor.
        Returns:
        a new Merge.MergeBuilder.

      • vote

        public static <T> ConflictResolution<T,​T> vote()
        Selects the highest weighted values. If a value occurs multiple times, the weight of all Sources is added. Multiple values from the same source count individually.

        These value retain their source tags.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the value.
        Returns:
        the most frequent values.
